    <h1>OLSP MineeMe: An Independent, Research-Based Review</h1>

    <p><strong>OLSP MineeMe</strong> is an AI-powered Chrome extension from the OLSP/GPT TOOLS 2 U ecosystem that automates Facebook comments and reactions using the user's own OpenAI API key. At a reported promotional price of $27/month (down from a stated regular price of $97/month), it installs in Chrome, connects to Facebook and an OpenAI key, and then runs in the background generating 2–4 line contextual comments and reactions on Facebook posts according to the user's preferred tone and custom prompts. Our short take: MineeMe does what it says on the label — it automates Facebook engagement — but every safety claim about how Facebook treats this kind of automation comes exclusively from the vendor, and no independent technical audit of account risk exists in the public domain. Buyers should weigh that gap carefully before subscribing.</p>

    <VerdictBox>
      <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Facebook-focused affiliate marketers and online business owners who are already active on the platform, have content worth surfacing, and want to reduce the manual time burden of daily engagement without outsourcing their voice entirely.</p>
      <p><strong>Not ideal for:</strong> anyone looking for a passive income tool, people who primarily use SEO or non-Facebook traffic strategies, or anyone unwilling to accept unverified vendor safety claims about Facebook account risk.</p>
    </VerdictBox>

    <h3>What Is It and Who Is It For?</h3>
    <p>MineeMe sits within Wayne Crowe's OLSP ecosystem as one of several optional "power tools" listed on the GPT TOOLS 2 U product hub, alongside tools like Leads Miner. The vendor markets it at Facebook content creators, affiliate marketers, coaches, and online business owners who are getting some traction on the platform but find it hard to maintain the daily engagement pace that Facebook's algorithm reportedly rewards. The core proposition is delegating the repetitive work of commenting and reacting to an AI layer — fed by the user's own OpenAI API key — so the profile stays active even when the user is offline.</p>

