  <section id="faq">
    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <FaqItem question="Does MineeMe risk getting my Facebook account restricted or banned?" answer="This is the most important question for any prospective buyer and the one with the least satisfying answer: we don't know, and neither does any independent reviewer. Facebook's Terms of Service prohibit automated engagement — comments, reactions, and other actions generated by software rather than a human. MineeMe's vendor addresses this by describing warm-up and cool-down pacing cycles designed to mimic natural human behavior, and explicitly states the tool is 'not a bot' and 'not a risky automation.' These are vendor assurances only. No independent technical audit has been published testing whether these controls prevent Facebook from flagging or actioning accounts. Anyone using MineeMe — or any Facebook automation tool — should treat account risk as real and unverified, not resolved by vendor marketing language." />
    <FaqItem question="Do I need a ChatGPT Plus subscription to use MineeMe?" answer="No — the vendor explicitly states that no ChatGPT Plus subscription is required. MineeMe uses a standard OpenAI API key, which is created through an OpenAI account with billing enabled. This is different from a ChatGPT Plus subscription. API usage is billed separately by OpenAI based on the number of tokens processed; for light daily engagement volumes this cost is likely modest, but it is an additional ongoing expense on top of the $27/month MineeMe subscription. Check current OpenAI API pricing before setting up to understand total monthly costs." />
    <FaqItem question="Is MineeMe a Facebook bot?" answer="The vendor explicitly says it is not: 'It's not a bot… not a spammer… not random actions.' From a technical standpoint, MineeMe is a Chrome extension that triggers AI-generated actions on Facebook based on user-defined prompts and timing controls. Whether Facebook's systems would classify it as automated activity — which its Terms of Service prohibit — is a separate question from how the vendor characterizes it. The distinction between 'a tool that automates Facebook actions' and 'a bot' may matter more for marketing purposes than for how Facebook's detection systems categorize the behavior." />
    <FaqItem question="What is the real monthly cost including the OpenAI API?" answer="The MineeMe subscription is $27/month at the promotional price. OpenAI API costs are additional and variable, based on the volume of comments generated and the AI model selected. For moderate daily engagement — say, 50–100 comments per day — OpenAI API costs at GPT-4o-mini rates would typically be a few dollars per month at current pricing, making total monthly cost approximately $30–$35. At higher volumes or with more capable (and expensive) models, costs increase proportionally. Verify current OpenAI API pricing independently, as rates change and depend on usage patterns." />
